<subSubSection id="DACA652BD45AB526FF7AB4F260F88B82" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45AB526FF7AB4F260F88B82" blockId="3.[151,1437,398,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FF7AB4F262548BE7" bold="true" box="[151,280,398,424]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FE12B4F261CC8BE7" authorityName="Singh &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="2022" box="[511,640,398,424]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Occipitotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FE12B4F261CC8BE7" box="[511,640,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Occipitotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is masculine and refers to the complete occipital carina on the head; “occipit” stands for occipital carina and “totus” (Latin for “complete”).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DACA652BD45AB526FF2AB4A96770898B" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45AB526FF2AB4A96770898B" blockId="3.[151,1437,398,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FF2AB4A962768BA0" bold="true" box="[199,314,469,495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Antenna with 22–30 flagellomeres (
<quantity id="55289B45D45AB526FD0DB4AA600A8BBF" box="[736,838,470,497]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.984999999999999" metricValueMax="7.62" metricValueMin="6.35" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" unit="in" value="27.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="25.0">25–30 in</quantity>
female; 
<quantity id="55289B45D45AB526FC47B4AA67428BBF" box="[938,1038,470,496]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="7.112" metricValueMin="5.588" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" unit="in" value="25.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="22.0">22–28 in</quantity>
male), longer than fore wing (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FA86B4AA63F6885B" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2(A–F). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, lateral view; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) apex of antenna; (D) base of antenna; (E) head, frontal view; (F) mesosoma, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D, E, F); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521271/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FF29B48663A4885B" box="[196,232,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4B</figureCitation>
), scapus small, subglobose, shorter ventrally than dorsally; occipital carina complete (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FB71B48667B4885B" box="[1180,1272,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FAEFB486666A885B" box="[1282,1318,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4C</figureCitation>
), ventrally straight or slightly curved reaching base of mandible (rarely reduced near base of mandible) and raised into a flange; remaining widely separated from hypostomal carina (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FD05B73E60298812" box="[744,869,578,605]" captionStart="FIGURES 6" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,184,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[160,1428,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 6(A–E). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., head, latero-posterior view. (A) Holotype, female; (B–E) paratypes. (B–D) females; (E) male. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521283/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 6A–E</figureCitation>
); hypoclypeal depression deep and small (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FAD4B73E66C38813" box="[1337,1423,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2(A–F). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, lateral view; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) apex of antenna; (D) base of antenna; (E) head, frontal view; (F) mesosoma, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D, E, F); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521271/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
); clypeus slightly convex or flat, not protruding beyond the level of the face (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FBEAB71A672888CF" box="[1031,1124,614,640]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2(A–F). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, lateral view; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) apex of antenna; (D) base of antenna; (E) head, frontal view; (F) mesosoma, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D, E, F); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521271/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); malar suture obsolescent; pronope large and deep (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FE5EB7F6614788EB" box="[435,523,650,676]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 3F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FDF4B7F6617188EB" box="[537,573,650,676]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4C</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum glabrous and shiny; notauli finely crenulate, terminating into rugose area posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FE5CB7D2615C8887" box="[433,528,686,712]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FDF2B7D2610A8887" box="[543,582,686,712]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4D</figureCitation>
); vein r of fore wing distinctly oblique and arising from basal 0.4–0.5 of pterostigma; first subdiscal cell of fore wing elongate (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FD11B7AE60C488A2" box="[764,904,722,749]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,597,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-216@7.[202,1385,597,1959]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5(A–D). (A, D) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, male. (A) Metasoma, dorsal view; (D) fore wing; (B–C) paratype, female. (B) fore wing; (C) hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521281/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 5B, 5D</figureCitation>
); fore wing vein 1-M of male widened, as wide as or slightly wider than length of cu-a (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FDB1B78A61FA895E" box="[604,694,758,785]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,597,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-216@7.[202,1385,597,1959]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5(A–D). (A, D) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, male. (A) Metasoma, dorsal view; (D) fore wing; (B–C) paratype, female. (B) fore wing; (C) hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521281/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
); propodeum coarsely rugose-reticulate, with weak median carina anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FEFEB6666227897B" box="[275,363,794,820]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) or entire; dorsal carinae of metasomal tergite I not united medially and tergite coarsely rugosereticulate with (feeble) (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FE43B642614A8917" box="[430,518,830,856]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) or without (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FD4FB64261B08917" box="[674,764,830,856]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
) median carina; metasomal tergite II longitudinally striate (nearly) complete (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FE9DB61E62818933" box="[368,461,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FE37B61E62B28933" box="[474,510,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4A</figureCitation>
) or anterior half striate (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FCF5B61E60388932" box="[792,884,866,893]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,597,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-216@7.[202,1385,597,1959]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5(A–D). (A, D) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, male. (A) Metasoma, dorsal view; (D) fore wing; (B–C) paratype, female. (B) fore wing; (C) hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521281/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); tergite II slightly longer than tergite III, feebly striate antero-laterally (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FE76B6FA62BD89EF" box="[411,497,902,928]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) or smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FD02B6FA600489EE" box="[751,840,902,929]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,597,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-216@7.[202,1385,597,1959]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5(A–D). (A, D) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, male. (A) Metasoma, dorsal view; (D) fore wing; (B–C) paratype, female. (B) fore wing; (C) hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521281/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); tergites IV–VI smooth and sparsely setose (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FAD0B6FA66DB89EF" box="[1341,1431,902,928]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FF7AB6D663F1898B" box="[151,189,938,964]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4A</figureCitation>
); length of ovipositor sheath 0.5–0.7 times as long as first tergite (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FC4FB6D660B2898B" box="[930,1022,938,964]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2(A–F). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, lateral view; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) apex of antenna; (D) base of antenna; (E) head, frontal view; (F) mesosoma, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D, E, F); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521271/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Figs 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FBE4B6D6677C898B" box="[1033,1072,938,964]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DACA652BD45AB526FF2AB6B166D08E7F" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45AB526FF2AB6B166D08E7F" blockId="3.[151,1437,398,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FF2AB6B1626D89A8" bold="true" box="[199,289,973,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Biology</emphasis>
. Host unknown, but collected from horsetails, 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FCBEB6B360BA89A7" box="[851,1014,974,1000]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Equisetaceae" genus="Equisetum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Equisetales" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FCBEB6B3608589A7" box="[851,969,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Equisetum</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FBE4B6B267ED89A7" box="[1033,1185,974,1000]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Equisetaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Equisetales" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Equisetaceae</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FB5CB6B2664789A7" box="[1201,1291,974,1000]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,196,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[151,1435,181,1191]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7(A–B). (A) Unidentified species of Coleoptera (Chrysomelidae); (B) horsetails, Equisetum sp. (Equisetaceae)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521285/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
) along with an unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FE25B68E610F8E43" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[456,579,1010,1036]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FDB9B68E604F8E43" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[596,771,1010,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D45AB526FCFDB68E60208E43" box="[784,876,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,196,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[151,1435,181,1191]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7(A–B). (A) Unidentified species of Coleoptera (Chrysomelidae); (B) horsetails, Equisetum sp. (Equisetaceae)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521285/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); considering the biology of other species of the members of this subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FE27B16A611B8E7F" box="[458,599,1046,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Exothecinae">Exothecinae</taxonomicName>
, it is likely to be an ectoparasitoid of coleopterous larvae on 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45AB526FB12B16B66D08E7F" box="[1279,1436,1046,1072]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Equisetaceae" genus="Equisetum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Equisetales" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FB12B16B66398E7F" box="[1279,1397,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Equisetum</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DACA652BD45AB526FF2AB14562878E1B" box="[199,459,1081,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45AB526FF2AB14562878E1B" blockId="3.[151,1437,398,1108]" box="[199,459,1081,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45AB526FF2AB14562158E1C" bold="true" box="[199,345,1081,1107]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Distribution</emphasis>
. Oriental.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
